


  Reports are "report cards" that aggregate data from other domains. Looking at the Report model, I see:
  - report_type: ReportType enum (TASKS, HABITS, GOALS, EVENTS, FINANCE, CHOICES)
  - user_uid: User the report belongs to
  - Reports aggregate metrics from domains

  For Reports, the relationships would be:
  1. (report)-[:AGGREGATES]->(domain_entity) - What entities this report aggregates
  2. (report)-[:REPORTS_ON]->(goal) - Goals this report covers
  3. (report)-[:GENERATED_FOR]->(user) - User this report belongs to (if not using user_uid field)

